en_1246769_0	An individual who had attempted to abduct and molest a little girl in a primary school in Puttalam was caught by the locals and handed over to the police.
en_1246769_1	The child had been abducted after the individual had said that the girl’s mother had asked him to bring the child home.
en_1246769_2	The individual was caught by locals while at a shrubbery area close to the Puttlam -Tiladiya railway line.
en_1246769_3	The locals stated that they caught him while he was taking the girl in to the woods.
en_1246769_4	The 8-year-old, girl who always travels home by three-wheeler after school, had been conned by this individual before being abducted.
en_1246769_5	A woman who had seen the girl travelling with an unknown person had informed of this to the girl’s mother over the telephone.
en_1246769_6	At that time, the man had taken the girl in to the woods near the Tiladiya Railway line.
en_1246769_7	The quick intervention of the locals prevented what could have been a very traumatic experience for the young girl, who was later handed over to the parents. According to police, the arrested suspect was a well-known felon in the area.
